    Two Sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov Test

    KolmogorovSmirnov.Rd

    Performs two sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test on data vectors.

    Super classes

    LearnNonparam::Permutation Test -> LearnNonparam::Two Sample Permutation Test -> Two Sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov Test

    • KolmogorovSmirnov$new()

    Method new()

    Create a new KolmogorovSmirnov object.

    Usage

    KolmogorovSmirnov$new(n_permu = NULL)

    Arguments

    n_permu

    an integer specifying how many permutations should be used to construct the permutation distribution. If NULL (default) then all permutations are used.

    Returns

    A KolmogorovSmirnov object.

    Method plot_ecdfs()

    Draw the empirical cumulative distribution function of each of the data fed.

    Usage

    Returns

    The object itself (invisibly).
